The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 Four bodies merge to isolate Lalus BCA

Patna: In order to isolate the Lalu Prasad Yadav-led Bihar Cricket Association, four separate cricket bodies which came into being after the bifurcation of Bihar state, decided on Thursday to merge for the promotion of cricket in state. 

The Association of Bihar Cricket led by former BJP MP and former Test cricketer Kirti Azad, Bihar Cricket Association (Patna) headed by dig of CRPF Alok Raj, Cricket Association of Bihar under the stewardship of Adhikari M. M. Prasad and Mrityunjay Tiwari-led Bihar Players Association merged and decided to register the new association under the companys act. 

Announcing this on Thursday, Azad, in the presence of Alok Raj, Prasad and Tiwari, declared that all four bodies had now become one. 

 (PTI) 




